t5052.text: He deserves all the happiness this world has to offer. So Cupid better do right by him. Cupid better be damn well on the mark... Happy Valentine’s Day, Future Boyfriend. I love you so, so, so very much, please don’t ever forget that.

t5053.text: And I never want to see him get hurt, not now, not ever.

t5054.text: I wish for him to find his soulmate and I wish for his soulmate to be worthy of him; because he is the most amazing, kind, sweet, caring, generous, gentle, cuddly, funny, charming, intelligent, handsome and talented man I have ever met.

t5055.text: I wish he would always be happy, I wish that he will never be alone and that he finds someone to love with his whole heart and that he finds someone who will love him unconditionally in return, even if that person is not me.

t5056.text: I promise to be his best friend, his biggest fan, his lover and to be a woman who loves him dearly and unconditionally; if he wants me, that is. I promise to always give him well wishes...

t5057.text: So, I settled on the only thing I know how to give, my love, a promise and a wish. A promise to love him as hard as I can for as long as I live. A promise to always support him and always be there when he needs me.

t5058.text: What on earth could I possibly give him that he doesn’t already have or that he couldn’t buy himself. I doubt he would settle for anything simple like chocolate or well, anything that I could actually give him. I’m not in the same league as him at all...

t5059.text: I’ve spend quite a long time trying hard to work out what to get Future Boyfriend for Valentine’s Day... I mean, what do you buy the man that has everything? I mean, Future Boyfriend is very well off.pic.twitter.com/v7iWtfgjSl
